        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:28PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Storrie Lake State Park, or 9 miles northeast of
Las Vegas, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of North Central San Miguel County.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 518 between Mile Markers 5 and 7.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 350 and 363.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 6 and 16.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
